<p>I am currently trying to make an application that uses the command <code>net share</code> from the CMD. However, when I press on the button that runs the code, it gives me the following error:</p>  <blockquote>   <p>An unhandled exception of type 'System.ComponentModel.Win32Exception' occurred in System.dll.</p> </blockquote>  <p>Here's the code I'm using:</p>  <pre><code>Process cmd = new Process(); cmd.StartInfo.FileName = "net share"; cmd.StartInfo.UseShellExecute = false; cmd.StartInfo.Arguments = txt_shareName + "=" + path; cmd.StartInfo.RedirectStandardOutput = true; cmd.Start(); txt_Logs.Text = cmd.StandardOutput.ReadToEnd(); </code></pre>  <p>But when you put <code>ipconfig</code> into the FileName part and <code>/all</code> into the Arguments part, it works perfectly.</p>